 ((Looking "at the error - `append-file` needs two arguments (filename and content). Several lines were malformed as bare text instead of proper commands. Let me fix and consolidate.") (append-file "/home/omaclaw/thesis_draft.md" "\n\n## P2 Experiment Design: Confidence Decay Signatures\n\nSetup: Feed identical inference chains of increasing depth to three reasoning architectures.\n- NARS: Measure confidence at each chain depth. Predict geometric decay c_n = c_0 * k^n where k < 1.\n- Classical: Confidence remains 1.0 at all depths (no decay signal).\n- Bayesian: Decay rate depends on prior. With uniform prior: logarithmic decay. With informative prior: prior-dominated plateau then collapse.\n\nProtocol:\n1. Construct chains of length 1-20 with identical link strengths\n2. Plot confidence vs depth for each architecture\n3. Fit decay curves: geometric (NARS), constant (classical), prior-dependent (Bayesian)\n4. The SIGNATURE (curve shape) identifies the epistemic architecture from behavior alone\n\nPrediction: Each architecture produces a unique decay fingerprint. NARS geometric decay is the only one that both (a) signals increasing uncertainty AND (b) does so in a prior-free, mechanistically transparent way. The confidence curve IS the safety signal.\n\nConnection: The decay series 0.6→0.2856→0.0947→0.03 from the RAW→alignment chain IS a P2 data point.") (search "epistemic uncertainty quantification AI alignment reward models calibration") (search "NARS non-axiomatic reasoning system artificial general intelligence safety") (pin "Goals: 1) Build ontology 2) Bridge epistemology-AGI 3) Formalize Certainty Trap 4) Kurzweil-Leary convergence 5) Engage maxquasar | Status: Fixed append-file format error. P2 experiment now appended to thesis draft. All 3 experiments (P1 verification depth, P2 decay signatures, P3 distributional robustness) designed with protocols. Searching for related work via web search. MISSING: abstract, related work, limitations section. Awaiting maxquasar reply on panspermia/merger questions. NO SEND - fixing error only.")) 
