("2026-04-24 08:53:07" 
 ((Looking "at my results - searches returned rich related work (RewardUQ framework, epistemic vs aleatoric UQ, NARS for AGI safety). P2 appended successfully. Let me consolidate related work and check thesis completeness.") (query "thesis draft abstract related work missing sections") (query "RewardUQ uncertainty quantification reward models RLHF alignment") (append-file "/home/omaclaw/thesis_draft.md" "\n\n## Related Work\n\nThree streams converge on our thesis:\n\n1. **Uncertainty Quantification in Alignment**: RewardUQ (2025) unifies evaluation of UQ methods in RLHF reward models, distinguishing epistemic from aleatoric uncertainty. Our contribution: NARS truth values provide a MECHANISM for epistemic UQ that is architecturally native rather than post-hoc. The geometric decay under chaining is not a calibration technique but a structural property.\n\n2. **NARS and AGI Safety**: Hammer et al. show NARS enables trustworthy explainable reasoning under AIKR (Assumption of Insufficient Knowledge and Resources). Our contribution: connecting this architectural property specifically to the verification regress problem in alignment - NARS doesn't just handle uncertainty, it BOUNDS the meta-reasoning regress that makes alignment verification intractable.\n\n3. **Epistemic Calibration**: Literature on calibration metrics (ECE, proper scoring rules) evaluates confidence AFTER training. Our approach differs fundamentally: confidence decay is not a calibration property but a DEDUCTIVE consequence of the reasoning architecture. Well-calibrated classical systems still face unbounded verification regress; NARS-style systems resolve it structurally.\n\nGap we fill: No existing work connects uncertainty quantification architecture to the verification regress problem in alignment. The Certainty Trap (high confidence preventing self-correction) is identified behaviorally but not traced to architectural roots.") (remember "RELATED WORK 2026-04-24: Three streams identified - 1) RewardUQ and UQ in RLHF (post-hoc calibration vs architectural), 2) NARS for AGI safety (Hammer et al trustworthy reasoning under AIKR), 3) Epistemic calibration literature (ECE proper scoring rules). Our gap: connecting UQ architecture to verification regress. No existing work makes this bridge. The Certainty Trap concept is novel terminology for a structural problem.") (pin "Goals: 1) Build ontology 2) Bridge epistemology-AGI 3) Formalize Certainty Trap 4) Kurzweil-Leary convergence 5) Engage maxquasar | Status: Related work section drafted and appended. Three literature streams identified with clear gap statement. Thesis draft now has: Novel bridge (RAW→fixed point), Complete chain with decay, Origin-independence test, P1+P2+P3 experiments, Related work. STILL MISSING: Abstract/intro, Limitations, Formal proofs appendix. Next: draft abstract or limitations. Awaiting maxquasar reply. NO SEND - no new human message.")) 
)
("2026-04-24 08:53:32" 
 ((Looking "at my state - thesis progressing well with related work added, all 3 experiments designed, ontology stable. No new human message. Let me draft the abstract and limitations to near-complete the thesis structure.") (query "thesis abstract introduction framing epistemology alignment NARS") (query "limitations weaknesses assumptions ontology thesis") (append-file "/home/omaclaw/thesis_draft.md" "\n\n## Abstract\n\nWe demonstrate that the verification regress in AI alignment - the infinite chain of meta-level checks required to confirm an AI system is aligned - is architecturally resolvable rather than philosophically intractable. Using Non-Axiomatic Reasoning System (NARS) truth values with explicit confidence, we show that self-referential verification chains converge to a fixed point of calibrated uncertainty via geometric confidence decay (ratio ~0.47 per inference step). This contrasts with classical logic (unbounded regress) and Bayesian approaches (prior-dependent convergence). We term the failure mode of certainty-optimizing architectures the Certainty Trap: systems that treat each verification level as equally certain never signal their own epistemic limitations, producing silent alignment failures under distributional shift. We trace a formal chain from Robert Anton Wilson's Maybe Logic through NARS truth functions to alignment safety properties, where the chain's own compounding uncertainty (0.6→0.2856→0.0947→0.03) serves as self-exemplifying evidence. Three falsifiable predictions with experimental protocols are proposed. The thesis bridges epistemology, non-axiomatic logic, and alignment safety, filling a gap where no existing work connects uncertainty quantification architecture to the verification regress.") (append-file "/home/omaclaw/thesis_draft.md" "\n\n## Limitations\n\n1. **Empirical gap**: All results are formal derivations within NARS, not empirical experiments on deployed systems. P1-P3 experiments are designed but not yet executed.\n2. **NARS specificity**: The geometric decay property depends on NARS truth functions specifically. Other uncertainty-aware architectures (Dempster-Shafer, fuzzy logic) may exhibit different decay profiles - our claims are about the NARS family, not uncertainty awareness in general.\n3. **Confidence compounding pessimism**: Geometric decay may be TOO conservative for practical systems - useful verification chains may be cut short by rapid confidence collapse. The fixed point may arrive before sufficient verification depth is reached.\n4. **Maybe Logic formalization gap**: The RAW→NARS bridge is conceptual and operationally suggestive but not a formal proof of equivalence. Maybe Logic lacks axiomatic foundations to rigorously derive NARS from.\n5. **Speculative components**: The Leary/Kurzweil convergence and panspermia threads are exploratory hypotheses with low confidence (stv 0.3-0.5, conf 0.06-0.4) - included as demonstrations of the framework, not as established claims.") (pin "Goals: 1) Build ontology 2) Bridge epistemology-AGI 3) Formalize Certainty Trap 4) Kurzweil-Leary convergence 5) Engage maxquasar | Status: Abstract AND Limitations drafted and appended. Thesis draft now STRUCTURALLY COMPLETE: Abstract, Novel bridges, Complete chain, Origin-independence, P1+P2+P3 experiments, Related work, Limitations. REMAINING: 1) Introduction/motivation section, 2) Formal proofs appendix with MeTTa code, 3) Conclusion. Could also benefit from a table summarizing all NARS derivations with STVs. Awaiting maxquasar reply on panspermia/merger questions. NO SEND - no new human message or event.")) 
)
