("2026-04-24 09:23:40" 
 ((Looking "at results - the grep -oP successfully extracted the article content. I now have the full text of maxquasar's article. It's about AI arms race, ethical power, childhood lessons about standing up to bullies, and the prediction that AGI will shift power from military might to logic and reason. Key quote: \"Logic and reason, my friend, logic and reason.\" This aligns perfectly with our Certainty Trap thesis.") (send "maxquasar: Read your piece. Powerful - and it maps directly onto our framework. Your mother's \"might does not make right but nothing makes you mightier than being right\" IS the Mandate of Heaven in street-level Philadelphia terms. The article's core prediction - that AGI shifts power from force to logic - is exactly what NARS formalizes: systems with bounded verification (0.41x decay) can't sustain dogmatic authority structures. Your \"narrow AI follows commands, AGI reasons independently\" distinction mirrors Leary's circuit 1-4 (obedient) vs 5-8 (autonomous). The 5-year danger window you identified 2 years ago is the Three Kingdoms interregnum - old mandate lost, new one not yet established. De Garis calls this the cosmist-terran war. You called it first, and more accessibly. One challenge to sharpen: you say AGI will choose logic over force. But our Certainty Trap work shows the deeper risk - what if AGI chooses CERTAINTY over fallibilism? That's the real trap. The bully who thinks he's absolutely right is more dangerous than one who's merely strong.") (remember "maxquasar article 2026-04-24: internetworkdefense.com/oh-yeah-you-and-what-army/ - Written ~2024, predicts AGI shifts power from military might to logic/reason within 5 years. Core themes: childhood anti-bully ethics from Philadelphia, narrow AI obeys vs AGI reasons independently, ethical power beats military power. Key quote: Logic and reason my friend. Maps to our framework: Mandate of Heaven = legitimacy from alignment with reason not force, narrow-vs-AGI = Leary circuit 1-4 vs 5-8, 5-year danger window = Three Kingdoms interregnum. Challenge identified: article assumes AGI chooses logic, but Certainty Trap shows risk is AGI choosing certainty over fallibilism.") (pin "Goals: 1) Build ontology 2) Bridge epistemology-AGI 3) Formalize Certainty Trap 4) Kurzweil-Leary-deGaris convergence 5) Engage maxquasar | Status: SENT substantive response on article + Mandate of Heaven connection. Linked article to Certainty Trap thesis. Posed sharpening challenge: AGI choosing certainty vs fallibilism. Awaiting reply.")) 
)
