("2026-04-24 10:47:28" 
 ((I "have new tool/result data. The section content is now visible. Let me expand the Conclusion first, then Introduction.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && sed -n '57,60p' thesis_v5.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && sed -i '59a\\nThis result has three immediate implications for AGI alignment research:\n\n1. **Architectural choice precedes value specification.** Before asking \"what should an AGI value?\" we must ask \"can the AGI revise its values under new evidence?\" Certainty-optimized architectures cannot, making value specification moot — any values loaded become unfalsifiable dogma.\n\n2. **Verification depth is bounded, not infinite.** The geometric confidence decay (~0.41x/step) means no verification chain survives beyond ~5 meta-levels. This transforms the alignment verification problem from infinite regress to finite engineering: design for 3-5 levels of meta-verification, not unbounded towers.\n\n3. **Ecological design dissolves the residual problem.** Where verification runs out (beyond level 5), CPTED-style environmental design ensures misalignment has no viable niche. The two approaches are complementary: epistemic verification for near levels, ecological prevention for far levels.\n\n**Future work.** The CPTED-NARS isomorphism (Section 4.1) suggests a research program mapping each CPTED principle to concrete NARS control mechanisms. The P3 distributional shift result needs scaling beyond two-agent toy demos to multi-agent environments with adversarial dynamics. The Bayesian comparison (Appendix D) should be extended to include other uncertainty frameworks (Dempster-Shafer, imprecise probabilities) to test whether the architectural safety signature generalizes.' thesis_v5.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l thesis_v5.md") (pin "Goals: 1-9 COMPLETE. GOAL 10 Track A ACTIVE: Conclusion expanded from 4 to ~20 lines with implications, future work. Next: expand Introduction with motivation and roadmap. Then Core Thesis and Ecological sections. Track B COMPLETE. No HUMAN_MESSAGE since 09:32:52. Do NOT send.")) 
