("2026-04-24 10:47:38" 
 ((I "have new tool/result data. The `sed -i` command failed with a syntax error due to complex quoting with newlines and embedded quotes. Let me fix the Conclusion expansion using a simpler approach — write to a temp file and insert it.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && sed -n '57,60p' thesis_v5.md") (write-file "/home/omaclaw/PeTTa/conclusion_expansion.txt" "This result has three immediate implications for AGI alignment research:\n\n1. **Architectural choice precedes value specification.** Before asking what should an AGI value we must ask can the AGI revise its values under new evidence. Certainty-optimized architectures cannot, making value specification moot — any values loaded become unfalsifiable dogma.\n\n2. **Verification depth is bounded, not infinite.** The geometric confidence decay (~0.41x/step) means no verification chain survives beyond ~5 meta-levels. This transforms the alignment verification problem from infinite regress to finite engineering: design for 3-5 levels of meta-verification, not unbounded towers.\n\n3. **Ecological design dissolves the residual problem.** Where verification runs out (beyond level 5), CPTED-style environmental design ensures misalignment has no viable niche. The two approaches are complementary: epistemic verification for near levels, ecological prevention for far levels.\n\n**Future work.** The CPTED-NARS isomorphism (Section 4.1) suggests a research program mapping each CPTED principle to concrete NARS control mechanisms. The P3 distributional shift result needs scaling beyond two-agent toy demos to multi-agent environments with adversarial dynamics.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && head -59 thesis_v5.md > thesis_v5_expanded.md && cat conclusion_expansion.txt >> thesis_v5_expanded.md && tail -n +60 thesis_v5.md >> thesis_v5_expanded.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l thesis_v5_expanded.md") (pin "Goals: 1-9 COMPLETE. GOAL 10 Track A ACTIVE: Expanding Conclusion via temp file insertion approach to avoid s