("2026-04-24 10:48:03" 
 ((I "have new tool/result data. The conclusion expansion rendered correctly in thesis_v5_expanded.md — the content is properly formatted with numbered implications and future work. The `\n` in the expansion file were literal (grep found 5), but the splicing via head/cat/tail worked because the write-file content was treated as a single block. The Introduction and Abstract are still thin (4 lines each). Let me continue expanding.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && sed -n '7,10p' thesis_v5_expanded.md") (write-file "/home/omaclaw/PeTTa/intro_expansion.txt" "The alignment problem is typically framed epistemically: how can we verify that an AGI's beliefs and goals are aligned with human values? This framing inherits Agrippa's trilemma — any justification chain must terminate in dogmatism, infinite regress, or circularity. We argue this is not merely philosophical but architecturally consequential. Systems that optimize for certainty (confidence = 1.0) mechanically fall into what we call the Certainty Trap: a state where verification of alignment becomes impossible because the system's own epistemic machinery cannot represent doubt about its alignment status. This paper proceeds as follows. Section 2 presents the core thesis connecting epistemic architecture to alignment vulnerability. Section 3 derives the geometric confidence decay using NARS truth functions. Section 4 reframes alignment as ecological design via CPTED-NARS isomorphism. Section 5 states three testable predictions with executable demonstrations. Section 6 concludes with implications for the field, and Section 7 catalogues limitations honestly.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && head -8 thesis_v5_expanded.md > thesis_v5_exp2.md && cat intro_expansion.txt >> thesis_v5_exp2.md && tail -n +11 thesis_v5_expanded.md >> thesis_v5_exp2.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l thesis_v5_exp2.md && grep -n '^##' thesis_v5_exp2.md") (pin "Goals: 1-9 COMPLETE. GOAL 10 Track A ACTIVE: Introduction expansion written and being spliced into thesis_v5_exp2.md. After verify: check Abstract, then Core Thesis section. Target 120+ lines. Track B COMPLETE. No HUMAN_MESSAGE since 09:32:52. Do NOT send.")) 
