("2026-04-24 10:48:28" 
 ((I "have new tool/result data. The Introduction expanded correctly with Agrippa's trilemma motivation and paper roadmap. The Abstract is already decent (4 lines covering problem/method/results). The Core Thesis section at lines 15-20 shows the formal derivation chain starting. Let me expand the Core Thesis with the sharpened argument about chain-decay vs revision-accumulation, then check overall line count.") (write-file "/home/omaclaw/PeTTa/core_expansion.txt" "An AGI optimizing epistemic confidence over calibrated uncertainty produces harder-to-detect misalignment. The verification regress (checking alignment of the alignment-checker) is a deductive chain, and NARS truth functions show such chains decay geometrically in confidence. Systems that suppress this decay (certainty-optimized) lose the architectural signal that bounds the regress. The critical distinction is between deductive chaining and evidential revision. Chaining compounds uncertainty: each meta-level multiplies confidence by ~0.41x, reaching noise floor by level 5-6. Revision accumulates evidence: repeated observation of the same claim drives confidence toward 1.0. The Certainty Trap occurs precisely when a system treats verification levels as revision (same claim re-evaluated) rather than chaining (new inference at each meta-level). A certainty-optimized system that assigns stv 1.0/0.99 to its own alignment cannot distinguish level-0 alignment from level-5 meta-alignment — both read 1.0/0.99. A fallibilist system using stv 0.8/0.8 sees level-0 at 0.8/0.8 but level-5 at 0.328/0.035, making the verification boundary architecturally visible.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && sed -n '15,18p' thesis_v5_exp2.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && head -14 thesis_v5_exp2.md > thesis_v5_exp3.md && cat core_expansion.txt >> thesis_v5_exp3.md && tail -n +19 thesis_v5_exp2.md >> thesis_v5_exp3.md") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l thesis_v5_exp3.md && grep -n '^##' thesis_v5_exp3.md") (pin "Goals: 1-9 COMPLETE. GOAL 10 Track A ACTIVE: Core Thesis expanded with chain-vs-revision distinction. thesis_v5_exp3.md being built. After verify: check total lines, assess if Abstract needs expansion or if 120+ target met. Track B COMPLETE. No HUMAN_MESSAGE since 09:32:52. Do NOT send.")) 
