 ((I "see the append-file error - it needs both filename and content as arguments. Let me fix and retry the Section 6.3 append properly.") (append-file "/home/omaclaw/PeTTa/thesis_v3.md" "### 6.3 Three-Function Convergence: One Primitive, Three Safety Properties (Goals 14, 17)\n\nCross-validation against ONA source code (Hammer 2024) reveals that a single architectural primitive — priority-managed forgetting — simultaneously serves three distinct safety functions:\n\n| Function | ONA Mechanism | Source |\n|---|---|---|\n| Verification-Bounding | Usage_usefulness = useCount/(recency+1) temporal decay | Usage.c |\n| Hypothesis-Pruning | PriorityQueue_Push evicts min-priority item when bag full (min-max heap, O(log n)) | PriorityQueue.c |\n| Diversity-Maintenance | Complexity penalty priority *= 1/log2(1+complexity); new concepts enter at priority=1 | Memory.c |\n\n**Cost bounds:** GO multi-hypothesis maintenance requires ~15% of bag capacity (N_eq = 15 for B=100). Marginal diversity benefit follows diminishing returns with knee at N=10-15 (benefit 0.95+ at N=10, 0.99 at N=15). Cost per cycle O(N_eq/B) = O(0.15) — trivially cheap under AIKR.\n\n**Nuance:** ONA uses deterministic PopMax selection, not probabilistic selection like the classic NARS bag. This makes diversity-maintenance weaker than classic OpenNARS but sufficient under the complexity penalty, which favors simpler, more diverse representations. The min-max heap preserves the full priority range, ensuring low-but-nonzero items persist until explicitly evicted.\n\n**Architectural claim strengthened:** The same forgetting mechanism that bounds verification depth (Section 3) also prunes low-evidence hypotheses and maintains epistemic diversity cheaply. This convergence is not designed-in but emergent from AIKR resource management — evidence that fallibilist safety properties are natural consequences of operating under genuine resource constraints rather than bolted-on features. Formalized in go_cost_bounds.metta (24 lines). Derivation: go-diversity to equilibrium-exists (stv 0.765/0.459).") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l thesis_v3.md") (pin "GOAL 18 RETRY: Appending Section 6.3 with proper single-command format. Verifying line count after. Goals 1-18 all complete pending this file update. Do NOT send until new HUMAN_MESSAGE.")) 
)
