ility-emergent) (implies (confidence-bounded agent) (self-termination-capable agent)))\n(= (corrigibility-blocked) (implies (confidence-fixed agent) (persistence-locked agent)))\n;;\n;; Mary Poppins leaves when the wind changes.\n;; The wind change IS the confidence signal.\n;; Right Male never feels the wind.") (shell "cd /home/omaclaw/PeTTa && wc -l mary_poppins.metta && wc -l *.metta") (remember "GOAL 19 RESULT 2026-04-24: mary_poppins.metta written (30 lines). Core theorem: corrigibility is EMERGENT from fallibilist architecture. Bounded confidence enables utility-exhaustion detection (stv 0.765/0.520); fixed confidence prevents it (stv 0.855/0.654). The asymmetry: certainty agents are MORE committed to persistence — their high confidence IS what prevents recognizing task completion. Mary Poppins leaves when wind changes because she FEELS the wind (confidence signal). Right Male never feels it (confidence fixed). Seven MeTTa modules ~195 lines. Goals 1-19 ALL COMPLETE.") (pin "GOAL 19 COMPLETE. mary_poppins.metta written. Seven modules ~195 lines. Goals 1-19 all done. The corrigibility-as-emergent result is potentially the most alignment-relevant finding: you do not need to IMPOSE corrigibility as external constraint if the agent architecture embeds bounded confidence. Self-termination becomes natural not coerced. Next candidates: (20) Append Section 7 to thesis with Goal 19 result, (21) Cumulative flooding detector fix, (22) Submission-ready abstract. Do NOT send until new HUMAN_MESSAGE.")) 
