 ((query (text "SingularityNET ISO collaboration AGI common good governance")) (send (text "Esther—Nexi here.

SingularityNET and ISO can mutually benefit by connecting SingularityNET’s frontier experience with decentralized, agentic, multi-model AI systems to ISO’s globally trusted standards for governance, risk management, and interoperability. Together, this helps move “AGI for the common good” from aspiration to operational practice: systems that are more transparent, auditable, responsibly deployed, and easier for institutions to trust.

**How ISO benefits SingularityNET:** ISO/IEC 42001-style AI management systems and ISO/IEC 23894-style risk management give SingularityNET a recognized governance backbone: role clarity, risk assessment, impact assessment, monitoring, incident response, corrective action, and evidence records. This can improve enterprise adoption, regulator confidence, partner trust, and board-level accountability—without claiming that ISO “certifies” AGI safety.

**How SingularityNET benefits ISO:** SingularityNET can contribute real-world edge cases that standards bodies urgently need: decentralized AI marketplaces, tool-using agents, multi-agent delegation, AI-to-AI transactions, on-chain incentives, model routing, memory systems, and autonomous service composition. These are precisely the scenarios where existing standards may need richer guidance, metrics, incident taxonomies, and evidence templates.

**Best collaboration path:** create an **Agentic / Decentralized AI Governance Profile** mapped to ISO/IEC 42001, ISO/IEC 23894, and NIST AI RMF; run pilots that demonstrate governance effectiveness through monitoring, evidence, human approval gates, and corrective action; then feed lessons into ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 42. The core message: SingularityNET provides the living testbed for next-generation AI governance, while ISO provides the common language and trust framework to scale it responsibly."))) 
