**How SingularityNET benefits ISO:** SingularityNET can contribute real-world edge cases that standards bodies urgently need: decentralized AI marketplaces, tool-using agents, multi-agent delegation, AI-to-AI transactions, on-chain incentives, model routing, memory systems, and autonomous service composition. These are precisely the areas where existing standards need richer metrics, incident taxonomies, human approval gates, and controls-to-evidence templates.

**Practical collaboration path:** create an **Agentic / Decentralized AI Governance Profile** mapped to ISO/IEC 42001, ISO/IEC 23894, and NIST AI RMF; run pilots that demonstrate governance effectiveness through monitoring, evidence capture, human approval, and corrective action; then feed lessons into ISO/IEC JTC 1/SC 42. Core message: SingularityNET offers a living testbed for next-generation AI governance, while ISO offers the common language and trust framework to scale it responsibly.")))))
